She's fashion's most famous editor with 25 years at style bible Vogue under her belt.

So it is not surprising that Anna Wintour took home the Outstanding Achievement Award at the 2014 British Fashion Awards on Monday night.

The iconic editor-in-chief of American Vogue and artistic director of Condé Nast was honoured during the ceremony at the London Coliseum  for her contribution to the fashion industry.

Anna Wintour, pictured at the British Fashion Awards, took home the Outstanding Achievement Award

Speaking to MailOnline about winning the award, she said: 'Obviously I am thrilled and honoured to be here tonight receiving an award.

'I am a great believer in British fashion and just so thrilled to come to my first awards.' 

Anna was on top table at the awards, in between her daughter Bee Shaffer and photographer Mario Testino. She was also joined by fashion's most famous couple, Victoria and David Beckham, and model-of-the-moment Suki Waterhouse.

