When the fashion guru's award was announced, Victoria, one of her biggest fans, cheered loudly, while Cara Delevingne raised her hands in the air in support of the industry heavyweight.

So close have Anna and Victoria, 40, become that Anna even acknowledged the British designer in her acceptance speech, where she cited her as one of the country's greatest talents.

Anna may have worked with the world's most esteemed models and designers and organised the Met Gala - showbiz's starriest night - but her career highlight? Being celebrated by Michelle Obama.

Speaking about her fashion highlights, she said: 'One of the most wonderful things that happened to me this year was having the costume centre at the Metropolitan Museum named in my honour and having the First Lady open it for me.'  

